        <h2>Text Alignment</h2>
        <p>
            You can change the text alignment of an element by adding
            <Code>text-left</Code>, <Code>text-right</Code>, <Code>text-center</Code> or <Code>text-justify</Code> to an element.
        </p>

        <p>
            Adding a breakpoint to the front of a text alignment class will cause it to only be applied on that size screen or larger.
            For example, <Code>medium-text-center</Code> will keep text left-aligned on the smallest screens,
            but switch to center-aligned on medium screens and larger.
